	<title>Daily Use Guide</title>
	<?dbhh topicname="HIDD_URL"?>
	<?dbhh topicname="HIDD_SVNPROGRESS"?>
	<simplesect>
		<para>
			This document describes day to day usage of the TortoiseGit client.
			It is <emphasis>not</emphasis> an introduction to version control
			systems, and <emphasis>not</emphasis> an introduction to Git. It is 
			more like a place you may turn to when you know	approximately 
			what you want to do, but don't quite remember how to do it.
		</para>
		<!--
		<para>
			If you need an introduction to version control with Git,
			then we recommend you read the fantastic book:
<ulink url="http://svnbook.red-bean.com/">
<citetitle>Version Control with Git</citetitle>
</ulink>.
		</para>
		-->
		<para>
			This document is also a work in progress, just as TortoiseGit and
			Git are. If you find any mistakes, please report them to
			the mailing list so we can update the documentation. Some of
			the screenshots in the Daily Use Guide (DUG) might not reflect the
			current state of the software. Please forgive us. We're working on
			TortoiseGit in our free time.
		</para>
		<para>
			In order to get the most out of the Daily Use Guide:
			<itemizedlist>
				<listitem>
					<para>
						You should have installed TortoiseGit already.
					</para>
				</listitem>
				<listitem>
					<para>
						You should be familiar with version control systems.
					</para>
				</listitem>
				<listitem>
					<para>
						You should know the basics of Git.
					</para>
				</listitem>
				<listitem>
					<para>
						You should have set up a server and/or have access
						to a Git repository.
					</para>
				</listitem>
			</itemizedlist>
		</para>
	</simplesect>
